 Animals]]'' || Stand-up special\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2004 || ''[[Politics (2004 film)|Ricky Gervais Live 2: Politics]]'' || Stand-up special\n|-\n| ''[[Alias (TV series)|Alias]]'' || Daniel Ryan || Episode: \"[[Alias (season 3)|Fa\u00e7ade]]\"\n|-\n| 2005\u20132013 || ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]'' (U.S.) || David Brent || 2 episodes; also executive producer\n|-\n| 2005\u20132007 || ''[[Extras (TV series)|Extras]]'' || Andy Millman || 13 episodes; also co-creator, writer, director and executive producer\n|-\n| 2006 || ''Ricky Gervais Meets...'' || Himself || 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2006, 2011 || ''[[The Simpsons]]'' || Charles Heathbar, Himself (voices) || 2 episodes; also writer\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Fame (2007 film)|Ricky Gervais Live 3: Fame]]'' || rowspan=\"3\" | Himself || Stand-up special\n|-\n| 2008 || ''Ricky Gervais: Out of England - The Stand-Up Special'' || Stand-up special\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2009 || ''[[Sesame Street]]'' || 3 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[SpongeBob SquarePants]]'' || Narrator (voice) || Episode: \"[[SpongeBob's Truth or Square]]\"\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[67th Golden Globe Awards]]'' || Himself (host) || Television special\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2010\u20132012 || ''[[The Ricky Gervais Show (animated series)|The Ricky Gervais Show]]'' || Himself (voice)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/the-ricky-gervais-show |title=The Ricky Gervais Show \u2013 Channel 4 |publisher=Channel 4 |accessdate=28 April 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100504075202/http://www.channel4.com/programmes/the-ricky-gervais-show |archive-date=4 May 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref> || 39 episodes; also co-creator, writer and executive producer\n|-\n| ''[[An Idiot Abroad]]'' || Himself || 21 episodes; also co-creator and executive producer\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2010 || ''[[Louie (U.S. TV series)|Louie]]'' || Dr. Ben || 2 episodes\n|-\n| ''Ricky Gervais: Out of England 2 - The Stand-Up Special'' || rowspan=\"2\" | Himself || Stand-up speci