ergman]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=''Thrills & Spills'' final host|years=2015}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[David Walliams]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{EmmyAward VoiceOver}}\n\n{{good article}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Castellaneta, Dan}}\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:21st-century American dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male writers]]\n[[Category:American people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Actors from Oak Park, Illinois]]\n[[Category:American male comedians]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male stage actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American television writers]]\n[[Category:American male video game actors]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Annie Award winners]]\n[[Category:Comedians from Illinois]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Chicago]]\n[[Category:Male actors of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Male television writers]]\n[[Category:Northern Illinois University alumni]]\n[[Category:Primetime Emmy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from Illinois]]\n[[Category:20th-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:27b0:4a01:eb80:6127:9625:dcdf:e71c", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dan_Castellaneta"}
